<li id="cite_note-bitgold-42">^ <a href="#cite_ref-bitgold_42-0"><sup><b>42.0</b></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-bitgold_42-1"><sup><b>42.1</b></sup></a> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web">Nick Szabo. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://unenumerated.blogspot.co.uk/2005/12/bit-gold.html">Bit gold</a>. "My proposal for bit gold is based on computing a string of bits from a string of challenge bits, using functions called variously "client puzzle function," "proof of work function," or "secure benchmark function.". The resulting string of bits is the proof of work.... The last-created string of bit gold provides the challenge bits for the next-created string."</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fzh.wikipedia.org%3A%E6%AF%94%E7%89%B9%E5%B8%81&amp;rft.aulast=Nick+Szabo&amp;rft.au=Nick+Szabo&amp;rft.btitle=Bit+gold&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Funenumerated.blogspot.co.uk%2F2005%2F12%2Fbit-gold.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
